## What the AI can do after connecting

| Tool | What it does |
|---|---|
| `list_files` | See all files in your project |
| `read_file` | Read any file directly |
| `write_file` | Write a fix directly to disk |
| `run_command` | Run python, pytest, npm, git |
| `undo` | Restore any file before AI touched it |

---

## How it works

```
Your laptop                   Claude / ChatGPT / Gemini
─────────────                 ─────────────────────────
Your project files  ←──⚡──→  AI reads your code
CodeBridge running            AI writes fixes back
port 7777                     Changes appear in your IDE
```

---

## Switch models anytime

Claude free limit finished? Same project. Go to ChatGPT or Gemini. Paste the same MCP URL. Continue from where you stopped.

---

## Dashboard

Open `http://localhost:7777` in your browser to see:
- All connected project files
- Live change log
- Connection status
- Apply or undo AI fixes

Works on mobile too — open on your phone while on the same WiFi.

---

## Chrome Extension (alternative)

No terminal needed. Install the extension, select your project folder, and the ⚡ badge appears on Claude.ai / ChatGPT / Gemini automatically.

See the `codebridge/` extension folder for setup.

